{
  "answer": "**Cordoba.**\n\nIn \"Bilad-e-Islamiya\" (Bang-e-Dara Part 3, ch. 2), Allama Iqbal addresses Islamic cities and lands in sequence: first Delhi (\"The soil of Delhi\"), then Baghdad (\"Baghdad, too, is worthy\"), and third Cordoba (\"The land of Cordoba, too, is the light of a Muslim's eye\").[^1]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [ch. 2 \"Bilad-e-Islamiya\"](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/#p-8c21df).",
